function kthLargestNumber(nums, k) {
    nums.sort((a, b) => {
        if (a.length == b.length) return a.localeCompare(b);
        return a.length - b.length;
    });
    return nums[nums.length - k];
}
```

    1. Sort the given nums array of strings based on their lengths (i.e., based on the number of digits). If the lengths are equal, sort the strings lexicographically.
2. Return the element at index (length - k), as it represents the kth largest number in the sorted array.

